modules.description: This module displays memory representations of heterogeneous OCaml values as terminal graphics, specifically targeting lists of labeled values with mixed types. It provides the `show` function to render these values directly in the Kitty terminal emulator. Use it to visualize complex data structures like lists of tuples containing different types, directly in the terminal.

This module visualizes the memory layout of OCaml values directly in the Kitty terminal emulator, handling both homogeneous and heterogeneous data structures through its core and child modules. It provides the `show` function to render labeled collections of values, supporting customizable display options such as color and layout direction. The child module extends this capability to mixed-type lists, enabling visualization of complex structures like lists of tuples with different types. Example use cases include inspecting the memory layout of lists, trees, or heterogeneous records during debugging or interactive exploration.
